Imagine you have a point on a graph, and you want to spin it clockwise 45 degrees around the center.  To do that, we use a special kind of number grid called a matrix.

The matrix that spins a point 45 degrees clockwise looks like this:

$$
\boxed{\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} & \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \\
-\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} & \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}
\end{bmatrix}}
$$

Think of it like a set of instructions for how to move the point!
